Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.31,0:02:10.27,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,0)\be1}The Sleeping Mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.70,0:02:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But someone has to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.24,0:02:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if someone does go, it'll just be the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.57,0:02:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It must mean that we're still not supposed\N to venture into the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.92,0:02:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mujika-dono{\i0} said so, too, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.75,0:02:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all the more reason to worry about his safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.08,0:02:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you having some kind of \Ntrouble regarding the mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.34,0:02:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.05,0:02:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.25,0:02:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Something seemed odd with the mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.29,0:02:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so I thought I could be of service.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.97,0:02:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey... a mushi-shi?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.44,0:02:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He says he's a mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.90,0:02:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.62,0:02:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.11,0:02:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.06,0:02:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, we've a favor to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.14,0:03:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you search for a mushi-shi by the name of Mujika, who resides deep in the mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.06,0:03:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For generations, a Guardian has lived \Nin the mountain who knows all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.94,0:03:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mujika-dono is the only person who understands the Guardian's wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been asking his advice whenever possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And, one of his instructions forbids us to go deep into the mountain during harvest time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, since Mujika-dono didn't come back to his den for quite some time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.51,0:03:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we broke that taboo, and several people went into the mountain in search of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But they soon fell ill of a high fever and nearly died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What life energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.32,0:04:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It seems a little sweet, or a little bitter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A stifling scent that sticks to my skin...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.75,0:04:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a path of the light vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.79,0:04:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a place where the river of life runs through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.25,0:04:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Moreover, it's harvest time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even an ordinary mountain's life energy will increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.31,0:04:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,2773)\i1}If a person goes in unprepared, he'll be hit by the energy and be bewildered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.35,0:04:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This being a path of the light vein, there should be a Guardian who is in control here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.34,0:04:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mountain's abnormalities are probably caused by changes in the Guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.68,0:04:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In which case, the said mushi-shi \Nshould know something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.33,0:04:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.47,0:04:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is this boy from the village?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.19,0:04:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.52,0:05:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.65,0:05:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've to find Mujika.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.67,0:05:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm... Mujika's apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.89,0:05:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So he has an apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.72,0:05:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold this between your back teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.45,0:05:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! B-bitter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.57,0:05:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You were supposed to bite it when you felt dizzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.56,0:05:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stimulant, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.40,0:05:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-you should've told me earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.80,0:05:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, just take it easy for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.06,0:05:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find your teacher for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.82,0:05:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What... are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.25,0:05:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mugura-nori...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.01,0:05:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are mushi called Mugura which are like the nerves of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.67,0:05:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to burrow my consciousness in them and run through the vegetation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.14,0:06:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.91,0:06:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.32,0:06:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this way. Go around...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.62,0:06:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to the opposite side of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.25,0:06:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.71,0:06:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.37,0:06:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He ripped the Mugura away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.26,0:06:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A-are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.72,0:06:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.53,0:06:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go... He's this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.10,0:06:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A bell? I guess it's around 4 o'clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.27,0:06:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't remember there being a bell in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He should be somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.39,0:07:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! {\alpha&HFF&}Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.19,0:07:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.69,0:07:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mujika!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.01,0:07:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And then? What happened \Nafter you slipped and hurt your leg?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.41,0:07:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I was eating the fruits and grasses around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.66,0:07:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I had water on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.69,0:07:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've troubled the villagers by being unable to let them know the Guardian's wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.51,0:07:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And on top of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.52,0:07:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...to be rescued by a fellow mushi-shi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.67,0:07:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.86,0:07:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Mujika.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.49,0:07:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a little embarrassed, but grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.50,0:07:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've thought of this mountain as my own backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.11,0:08:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But to have slipped in such a place... I'm getting old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.65,0:08:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it's time for me to give up my duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.37,0:08:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean as Guardian of the mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.89,0:08:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one who can rip Mugura\N mushi off from an invader
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is either the true guardian of the place
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.47,0:08:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or someone who is exercising the guardian's powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.57,0:08:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the mountain was undergoing unusual changes was because you, the guardian,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't exercise your powers since you were unable to move from the bottom of the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.15,0:08:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think I can somehow continue my guardian duties tomorrow despite my leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.38,0:08:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The mountain will go back to being normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.99,0:08:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I hear that it's difficult for a human \Nto assume the role of a guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.89,0:08:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Were there extenuating circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.39,0:08:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you're aware by now, \Nbut this is a path of the light vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.84,0:08:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There used to be a rightful guardian who could suppress the mountain's energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.64,0:09:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But a villager killed it by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.89,0:09:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The waters of the river began to smell like sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.39,0:09:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and the vegetation started to over-ripen and rot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.57,0:09:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I, too, was a traveling mushi-shi in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I began to stop by this village frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.44,0:09:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the villagers in trouble and decided to become the guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.48,0:09:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife wasn't able to live long, perhaps because of the mountain's life energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're planning to make that boy the next guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.62,0:09:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd sure footing on the mountainous terrain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.81,0:09:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He was born of the mountain \Nand raised on the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.86,0:09:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw how many children \Nthere were in the village, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.06,0:09:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the water flowing from this mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.76,0:10:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the women are constantly giving birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.59,0:10:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But they can't raise all the children, \Nso some are abandoned in the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.85,0:10:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This boy is the only one who survived \Nnot getting eaten by a wild beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.78,0:10:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But his siblings, who remained \Nin the village, all died young.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.25,0:10:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a year since his parents found out\Nthat he was alive, and brought him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.38,0:10:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, but it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.52,0:10:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's surely for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.02,0:10:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The ringing of a bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.50,0:10:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This late at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you always been a wandering mushi-shi who's never laid down roots?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.21,0:10:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.61,0:10:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've a tendency to attract mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.86,0:10:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If I live too long in one place,\Nit'll end up becoming a nest for mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I learned how to drive mushi away out of necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.57,0:11:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I guess you've no choice \Nbut to be a rolling tumbleweed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.83,0:11:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.73,0:11:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It suits my personality and it's not a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.81,0:11:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From the viewpoint of someone who is unable to set foot outside of this mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.61,0:11:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a bit jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.99,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For better or for worse, this mountain will be the final resting place for my bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.42,0:11:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay then... I'll go back to let \Nthe others know what's going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.42,0:11:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't overdo yourself while I'm gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.41,0:11:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't you come back until the restriction period for entering the mountain is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.89,0:11:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you take care, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:11:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, stay well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.87,0:12:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mujika...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.09,0:12:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still your apprentice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.07,0:12:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. Even the trek here \Nfrom the village can be training.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're on track to be one helluva mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.11,0:12:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.51,0:12:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! The mushi-shi is back! \NAnd Kodama is with him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.08,0:12:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mujika-san is safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's getting closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.04,0:12:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And it's not because of the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:12:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Where on earth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.00,0:12:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.64,0:13:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is strange about that sound.\NThere are no bells around these parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and my dad and the others are saying \Nthey can't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it's some kind of mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.75,0:13:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you already learned how to become Guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.73,0:13:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.07,0:13:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about the way \Nfor a human to become a guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.43,0:13:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,By keeping the Mugura mushi inside your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.90,0:13:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in a state of constantly performing Mugura-nori.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even while you're sleeping,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.85,0:13:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all things that are sensed by \Nthe mountain flow into your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.05,0:13:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you bear it and become able to control Mugura,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.81,0:13:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll even gain the power to restrain \Nthe mountain's unusual energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.90,0:13:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't learned that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.70,0:13:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.13,0:13:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the source of the bell is a mushi \Nand you don't have to worry too much about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.35,0:14:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home and get back to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.48,0:14:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where're you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.12,0:14:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in the middle of a stroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.98,0:14:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.80,0:14:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mountain... is completely silent...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.54,0:14:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means that {\i1}it{\i0} is right around the corner...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.52,0:14:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The old man is calling over something terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.97,0:14:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.28,0:14:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That sound... it's heading towards...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.44,0:14:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The summit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.99,0:15:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you still have business with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.14,0:15:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your foot's not injured, is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All that time, you were beckoning \Na {\i1}Kuchinawa{\i0} in that inconspicuous place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.25,0:15:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.79,0:15:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That bell-like sound that's getting closer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.97,0:15:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the cry of a {\i1}Kuchinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mushi that eats guardians...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.03,0:15:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a mushi that eats mountain and swamp guardians
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.31,0:15:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and takes their place as guardians.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.95,0:15:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also a mushi which brings stability to land.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.26,0:15:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my mission to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.13,0:15:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.53,0:15:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The previous Guardian was a magnificent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.84,0:15:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a beautiful guardian whose \Nfigure was that of a giant old boar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.14,0:15:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I am... to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.83,0:16:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have said what I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.63,0:16:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Save the details for later. \NGet off this mountain now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.06,0:16:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.96,0:16:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}Kuchinawa{\i0} has already found me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.33,0:16:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A creature like the {\i1}Kuchinawa{\i0} \Nought to sit in the guardian's seat...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.61,0:16:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as it's too difficult for a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What I taught Kodama is just \Nthe wisdom he needs to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.80,0:16:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.90,0:16:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm ripping the {\i1}Mugura{\i0} from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.23,0:16:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.86,0:16:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you could do that, there's no other recourse...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.63,0:16:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be something, other than doing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.92,0:16:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the villagers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.60,0:16:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They revere you... need you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you were a little envious of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.79,0:16:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but the truth is, I was a little envious of you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.12,0:16:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just decide to die by yourself like this!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.65,0:16:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.49,0:17:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll only get yourself dragged in!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.47,0:17:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.94,0:17:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mujika?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.82,0:17:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mujika!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.61,0:17:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Mujika's back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.45,0:17:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mujika!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.99,0:17:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Saku...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.68,0:17:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.05,0:17:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.15,0:17:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone. How's the mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.01,0:17:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there have been several\Nstrange occurrences this year, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.25,0:18:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate your coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.59,0:18:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mujika. Can't you come live in our village?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.66,0:18:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We need you here in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.42,0:18:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.36,0:18:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.54,0:18:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I've the tendency to draw out mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.13,0:18:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If I live in one place for too long,\Nit'll become a nest for mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.90,0:18:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there any way around it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.71,0:18:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Saku... my younger sister...\Nshe's always waiting for your return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.85,0:18:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you settle down with her here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.49,0:18:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one way for me to be able to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.87,0:18:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's for me to kill and eat \Nthe mountain guardian and take its place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll be able to keep mushi off \Nthe mountain with my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.58,0:19:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to live here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.06,0:19:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's no way that it can happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My map of the Guardian's \Npathway and poison are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.41,0:19:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When did they go missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.27,0:19:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Saku! Where have you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.28,0:19:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... I got... some boar meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.01,0:19:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make a hot pot with it right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.91,0:19:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll just be a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.19,0:19:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make a really good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.72,0:19:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Saku...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.85,0:19:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.86,0:19:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So tell me you won't ever leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.81,0:20:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I dreamed about something \Nthat certainly isn't part of my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.77,0:20:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When I arrived at the summit, \Nyou were on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.27,0:20:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and Mujika was nowhere to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.24,0:20:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked for him everywhere, but I couldn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.49,0:20:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't a trace of his den either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.67,0:20:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And not one villager remembers who Mujika was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Once a guardian is eaten by {\i1}Kuchinawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.15,0:20:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,previous guardian is replaced \Nby a new one, that's what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Only those who were on the mountain\Nat the time will have their memories intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.21,0:20:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Was it you who prepared this mushi repellent?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.49,0:21:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.46,0:21:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, I'm impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.74,0:21:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.78,0:21:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I'm Mujika's apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.01,0:21:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kodama...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.91,0:21:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a tree which the others can't seem to cut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.41,0:21:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to know if you have any ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.39,0:21:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.79,0:21:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.79,0:21:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.90,0:21:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Brr, it's cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.71,0:21:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's no other recourse!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.71,0:21:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There must be something, other than doing this!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.86,0:21:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He was right... unfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.59,0:22:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What a majestic being.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.36,0:22:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it couldn't care less what humans think.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.06,0:22:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Kuchinawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.75,0:22:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As if yawning, the Kuchinawa gave a single cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.88,0:22:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and thereafter his stomach just heaved in silence.
